Nursing Home Chain RHM’s Owners Hire Underwriters for LBO Loans

-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 
2011-04-20T10:06:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/nursing-home-chain-rhm-s-owners-hire-underwriters-for-lbo-loans.html
UniCredit SpA is leading
underwriters financing  Waterland Private Equity Investments BV ’s
buyout of  RHM Group , a German nursing home care provider.  GE Capital  and NIBC Bank NV helped UniCredit to raise 135
million euros ($195 million) of senior leveraged loans for
Deidesheim, Germany-based RHM, UniCredit said in a statement
today.  Waterland said in December it agreed to buy RHM to expand
its share in the German care and rehabilitation market. RHM
operates 13 clinics for rehabilitation and eight nursing homes
with about 1,900 beds in total, according to the statement.  Details of the financing are as follows:  To contact the reporter on this story:
